  "Magnesium cannot bond with oxygen": "",
  "Mg²⁺ and O²⁻ already balance 1:1, so the formula should be MgO": "",
  "Mg²⁺ and O²⁻ both have magnitude 2, so criss-cross gives Mg₂O₂, which reduces to MgO. One-to-one ratio already balances charges.": "",
  "Write the formula for ammonium sulfate given NH₄⁺ and SO₄²⁻.": "",
  "(NH₄)₂SO₄": "",
